      "content": "Even if your symptoms have disappeared, the antibiotic may not have eliminated all the bacteria, necessitating the full course to prevent recurrence. Discontinuing early significantly increases the risk of treatment failure and developing antibiotic resistance. While gut health is important, interfering with the full prescribed course undermines the treatment's effectiveness. Always follow your doctor's dosing schedule strictly, as they determined the necessary duration for your specific infection.",
      "source": "target",
